cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.IT, cs.CE 

This paper is primarily focused on the networking aspects of the Tactile Internet, specifically on enabling edge cooperation through resource sharing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses computation and caching, which could fall under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.SY (Systems and Control), respectively. The optimization problem formulation and solution could be categorized under cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science).
